    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; however, the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition is the regulatory standard for this device class and the primary basis for the 510(k) submission. The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA model adequately predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the pre-specified acceptance bounds. Decision: Accepted.",
